The course gives an overview of the most important sub-fields and topics of the anthropological research, illustrated by the examples from major authors/studies. Students can practice an anthropological approach in their own individual research projects.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course provides an overview of the anthropological perspective to the study of religions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course students know the core concepts and approaches of the discipline and are able to implement anthropological tools to study contemporary religious phenomena.
